r%20to%20revolution.%20The%20new%20generation%20is%20heir%20to%20a%20national%20tradition%20of%20political%20violence%20and%20subversion%20that%20dates%20back%20centuries.%20%26quot%3BToday's%20Russian%20oppositionists%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20similar%20situation%20to%20their%2019th-century%20forefathers%3A%20that%20the%20move%20to%20violence%20is%20in%20part%20a%20result%20of%20a%20closing%20of%20'normal'%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20Sean%20Guillory%2C%20a%20historian%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20use%20of%20violence%20is%20to%20accelerate%20the%20revolutionary%20clock.%26quot%3B%20For%20Ammosov%20and%20the%20other%20combatants%2C%20the%20question%20isn't%20whether%20violent%20revolution%20is%20justified.%20It's%20whether%20violence%20has%20any%20chance%20of%20success%20where%20all%20else%20has%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Ammosov%20agreed%20to%20speak%20with%20me%2C%20he%20said%20I%20needed%20to%20talk%20to%20his%20friend%20and%20associate%20who%20first%20vetted%20him%20for%20the%20anti-Putin%20cause%3A%20Denis%20Sokolov%2C%20the%20leading%20recruiter%20for%20today's%20generation%20of%20violent%20Russian%20revolutionaries.%20In%202022%2C%20Sokolov%20founded%20the%20Civic%20Council%2C%20a%20Warsaw-based%20group%20that%20helps%20recruit%2C%20screen%2C%20and%20transport%20Russians%20to%20fight%20Putin's%20troops%20in%20Ukraine.%20A%20social%20anthropologist%20with%20a%20specialty%20in%20Russia's%20restive%20North%20Caucasus%20region%2C%20he%20served%20as%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20prestigious%20Kennan%20Institute%20at%20the%20Wilson%20Center%20in%20Washington.%20He%20was%20also%20an%20associate%20of%20Galina%20Starovoytova%2C%20a%20dissident%20who%20was%20assassinated%20in%201998%20in%20a%20killing%20organized%20by%20a%20former%20GRU%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20collapsed%20in%201991%2C%20Sokolov%20told%20me%2C%20he%20began%20to%20think%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20future%20for%20Russia.%26quot%3B%20The%20problem%20was%20that%20entrenched%20Soviet-era%20elites%2C%20including%20bureaucrats%20and%20ex-KGB%20officers%2C%20were%20carving%20out%20a%20system%20of%20%26quot%3Bstate%20capitalism%26quot%3B%20that%20was%20severely%20impeding%20the%20nation's%20progress.%20He%20came%20to%20support%20independence%20for%20any%20region%20of%20Russia%2C%20including%20Ammosov's%20Sakha%2C%20with%20a%20capacity%20for%20%26quot%3Bself-rule.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223228%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Denis%20Sokolov.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d22bbd1d8d2deb96b7e33c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDenis%20Sokolov%2C%20the%20leading%20recruiter%20for%20today's%20generation%20of%20Russian%20revolutionaries%2C%20has%20come%20to%20believe%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20future%20for%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESimona%20Supino%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20our%20conversation%2C%20Sokolov%20was%20joined%20by%20his%20close%20associate%20Anastasia%20Sergeeva.%20From%202009%20to%202016%2C%20Sergeeva%20served%20as%20the%20Moscow%20program%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Republican%20Institute%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20funded%20by%20the%20US%20government%20that%20aims%20to%20foster%20democracy%20around%20the%20world.%20Washington%2C%20of%20course%2C%20has%20a%20long%20and%20checkered%20history%20of%20recruiting%2C%20funding%2C%20and%20arming%20insurgents%20pitted%20against%20America's%20global%20adversaries.%20But%20when%20I%20asked%20Sokolov%20and%20Sergeeva%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-cia-officer-andrew-bustamante-explains-how-spying-works-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20CIA%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20supporting%20their%20revolutionary%20activities%2C%20they%20both%20scoffed.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20afraid%2C%26quot%3B%20Sokolov%20said%20%E2%80%94%20scared%20of%20riling%20the%20Kremlin.%20Russian%20businessmen%20are%20bankrolling%20his%20efforts%2C%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20but%20he%20declines%20to%20name%20any%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESergeeva%20shares%20her%20assessment%20of%20what%20is%20spurring%20Russians%20to%20turn%20against%20Russia.%20Under%20Putin's%20rule%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20country%20is%20closed.%26quot%3B%20For%20a%20Russian%20man%20of%20fighting%20age%2C%20there%20are%20two%20options.%20One%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bsell%20his%20life%20expensively%26quot%3B%20by%20taking%20a%20cash%20bonus%20to%20join%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20has%20taken%20the%20lives%20of%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20Russian%20soldiers.%20The%20other%20is%20%26quot%3Bto%20escape%20from%20the%20country%20and%20forget%20about%20everything.%26quot%3B%20That%20bleak%20choice%2C%20Sergeeva%20added%2C%20leaves%20many%20Russian%20men%20%26quot%3Bfrustrated%26quot%3B%20by%20an%20immovable%20%26quot%3Bweight%26quot%3B%20pressing%20on%20them.%20The%20Russians%20have%20a%20word%20for%20this%20particular%20type%20of%20distress%3A%20toshno%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20literally%20means%20a%20physical%20feeling%20of%20nausea%20%E2%80%94%20completely%20sick%20of%20the%20state%20of%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20sort%20of%20man%2C%20Sokolov%20chimed%20in%2C%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20stand%20the%20situation.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BHe%20can't%20look%20in%20the%20mirror%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BHe%20feels%20loneliness%20in%20Russia%2C%20where%20everyone%20else%20supports%20the%20war.%26quot%3B%20To%20volunteer%20to%20fight%20alongside%20fellow%20Russians%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20to%20seek%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bbrotherhood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20an%20example%20of%20this%20type%20of%20man%2C%20Sokolov%20pointed%20me%20to%20a%20businessman%20in%20his%20early%2050s%20who%20goes%20by%20Valter%2C%20his%20military%20call%20name.%20After%20volunteering%20to%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20he%20was%20wounded%20in%20action%20and%20is%20now%20recuperating%20in%20Kyiv.%20When%20I%20contacted%20him%20via%20WhatsApp%2C%20Valter%20told%20me%20he%20is%20divorced%2C%20with%20an%20adult%20daughter.%20By%20his%20mother%2C%20he%20is%20an%20ethnic%20Ukrainian.%20The%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20made%20him%20feel%20like%20%26quot%3Ban%20accomplice%20to%20an%20incredible%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20he%20knew%20that%20going%20to%20war%20against%20Putin%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20devil%20himself%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20would%20permanently%20sever%20his%20ties%20to%20his%20family%20in%20Russia.%20But%20now%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20look%20at%20myself%20in%20the%20mirror.%26quot%3B%20He%20shared%20photos%20of%20his%20multiple%20bullet%20wounds%2C%20including%20a%20gaping%20gash%20in%20his%20upper%20left%20arm%20and%20bone%20fragments%20in%20his%20hand.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20I%20will%20return%20to%20the%20front%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20activity%20of%20my%20hand%20is%20restored%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224733%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Tatiana%20Kosinova.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d22b8e1d8d2deb96b7e333%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223155%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETatiana%20Kosinova%20helps%20recruit%20Russians%20to%20fight%20against%20their%20countrymen%20in%20Ukraine.%20Putin%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20be%20overthrown%2C%20killed%2C%20destroyed.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESimona%20Supino%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Warsaw%2C%20I%20met%20with%20Tatiana%20Kosinova%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20a%20volunteer%20now%20fighting%20against%20Russian%20forces%20in%20Ukraine.%20In%20Russia%2C%20she%20worked%20for%20Memorial%2C%20a%20now%20disbanded%20group%20cofounded%20by%20the%20human-rights%20activist%20Yelena%20Bonner%20that%20documented%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Gulag.%20After%20fleeing%20the%20country%20with%20her%20son%20in%202022%2C%20she%20met%20Sokolov%20in%20Warsaw%20and%20began%20helping%20him%20recruit%20volunteer%20fighters.%20Her%20son%2C%20she%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bwanted%20to%20be%20in%20the%20first%20group%20of%20our%20volunteers%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20proud%20of%20this.%26quot%3B%20As%20for%20Putin%2C%20he%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Busurper%2C%20bandit%2C%20and%20fascist%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20who%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20be%20overthrown%2C%20killed%2C%20destroyed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20resorting%20to%20armed%20rebellion%20is%20the%20culmination%20of%20a%20lifetime%20of%20disillusionment%20with%20the%20Kremlin.%20On%20a%20video%20call%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpictures-photos-kyiv-ukraine-before-war-russia-history-rus-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKyiv%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20fighter%20who%20goes%20by%20Itil%20told%20me%20he%20is%20a%20Crimean%20Tatar%20who%20was%20born%20in%20Moscow%20in%201979.%20He%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20circus%2C%20the%20family%20business%2C%20and%20performed%20as%20an%20acrobat%20all%20over%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20His%20father%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bbadass%26quot%3B%20who%20hated%20the%20USSR.%20Over%20shortwave%20radio%2C%20the%20family%20listened%20to%20the%20Voice%20of%20America.%20Itil%20says%20he%20served%20as%20a%20high-ranking%20clerk%20in%20a%20military%20command%20center%20tasked%20with%20planning%20Russia's%20response%20to%20a%20nuclear%20attack%20by%20a%20hostile%20power.%20Inspired%20by%20his%20idol%2C%20the%20charismatic%20liberal%20politician%20Boris%20Nemtsov%2C%20Itil%20became%20active%20in%20anti-Putin%20demonstrations.%20But%20when%20a%20buddy%20was%20arrested%20and%20jailed%2C%20for%20pushing%20a%20police%20officer%20at%20a%20street%20protest%2C%20Itil%20fled%20to%20Ukraine%20to%20avoid%20a%20similar%20fate.%20(Nemtsov%20was%20assassinated%20on%20a%20bridge%20near%20the%20Kremlin%20in%202015.)%20For%20him%2C%20Russia's%202022%20full-scale%20invasion%20was%20the%20tipping%20point.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20children%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20going%20mad.%26quot%3B%20He%20signed%20up%20to%20fight%20against%20Russian%20soldiers.%20These%20days%2C%20he%20works%20mainly%20behind%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20tending%20to%20wounded%20volunteers%20in%20Kyiv%20hospitals.%20In%20the%20event%20that%20Russian%20armed%20forces%20overrun%20Ukraine%2C%20he%20plans%20to%20evacuate%20his%20Ukrainian%20wife%20and%20her%20daughter%2C%20who's%20from%20a%20previous%20relationship.%20As%20for%20himself%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20not%20run%20again.%20My%20fear%20is%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internet%20has%20made%20the%20job%20of%20recruiting%20revolutionaries%20far%20easier%20than%20it%20was%20in%20the%20days%20when%20Vladimir%20Lenin%20and%20his%20fellow%20Bolsheviks%20in%20exile%20frequented%20the%20coffee%20shops%20of%20Europe.%20Even%20in%20%26quot%3Bclosed%26quot%3B%20Russia%2Cthe%20Civic%20Council%20can%20be%20found%20on%20a%20Telegram%20channel.%20There%2C%20instructions%20for%20anyone%20who%20wants%20%26quot%3Bto%20fight%20against%20Putin%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%20are%20plain%20enough%3A%20%26quot%3BRegister%20an%20e-mail%20address%20on%20ProtonMail%20and%20fill%20our%20application%20form.%26quot%3B%20Most%20applicants%20live%20in%20Russia%2C%20Sokolov%20tells%20me%2C%20but%20submissions%20have%20come%20from%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Uruguay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20apply%20from%20inside%20Russia%20are%20instructed%20to%20get%20to%20a%20former%20Soviet%20republic%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20Armenia%2C%20Georgia%2C%20or%20Kazakhstan%20%E2%80%94%20that%20Russian%20citizens%20can%20enter%20without%20a%20visa.%20Once%20they're%20there%2C%20Sokolov%20subjects%20them%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20background%26quot%3B%20interview%20via%20remote%20video%20from%20his%20post%20in%20Warsaw.%20To%20weed%20out%20the%20Kremlin's%20spies%2C%20he%20asks%20the%20applicants%20about%20their%20motives%20for%20seeking%20to%20enlist%20and%20grills%20them%20on%20their%20biographical%20details.%20Sokolov%20says%20those%20working%20for%20Russia's%20security%20service%2C%20the%20FSB%2C%20invariably%20trip%20over%20some%20aspect%20of%20their%20cover%20story.%20They%20%26quot%3Balways%20make%20a%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224907%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Anastasia%20Sergeeva.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d234261d8d2deb96b7e8c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223271%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnastasia%20Sergeeva%2C%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20cause%2C%20says%20Russian%20men%20face%20two%20options%3A%20die%20fighting%20for%20Putin%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20or%20flee%20the%20country%20and%20%26quot%3Bforget%20about%20everything.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESimona%20Supino%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EApplicants%20who%20pass%20the%20interview%20stage%2C%20some%2070%25%2C%20are%20told%20to%20wait%20as%20their%20transit%20to%20Ukraine%20is%20worked%20out.%20Sokolov%20works%20with%20Ukrainian%20military%20authorities%20to%20discreetly%20move%20the%20recruits%20in%20batches%20of%20about%2020%20at%20a%20time%2C%20roughly%20every%2030%20days.%20Once%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20recruits%20are%20subjected%20to%20additional%20methods%20of%20verification%2C%20including%20a%20lie-detector%20test.%20Those%20who%20pass%20are%20asked%20to%20sign%20a%20contract%20with%20Ukraine's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2C%20put%20on%20the%20payroll%2C%20and%20dispatched%20to%20training%20camps%20at%20secret%20locations.%20From%20there%2C%20they%20go%20to%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20attached%20to%20a%20brigade%20composed%20of%20fellow%20Russians%20but%20headed%20by%20a%20Ukrainian%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20the%20system%20has%20proved%20far%20from%20smooth.%20Initially%2C%20Sokolov%20recruited%20Russians%20for%20an%20existing%20brigade%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Russian%20Volunteer%20Corps.%20But%20the%20RDK%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20made%20up%20largely%20of%20what%20Sokolov%20calls%20%26quot%3Bfar-right%26quot%3B%20types%2C%20including%20Nazis%2C%20who%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20liberty%20and%20freedom%20of%20thought%20as%20proclaimed%20by%20the%20European%20Convention%20on%20Human%20Rights.%20They%20insisted%2C%20for%20example%2C%20on%20%26quot%3Bclear%20blood%20criteria%26quot%3B%20for%20determining%20who%20is%20a%20Russian.%20Sokolov%20also%20believes%20the%20brigade%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Binfiltrated%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20FSB.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Sokolov%20cut%20ties%20with%20the%20RDK.%20With%20his%20Ukrainian%20contacts%2C%20he%20established%20a%20new%20brigade%2C%20the%20Siberian%20Battalion%2C%20with%20Ammosov%20as%20a%20leader.%20But%20Ukrainian%20military%20intelligence%2C%20Sokolov%20says%2C%20kept%20the%20unit%20on%20too%20tight%20a%20leash%2C%20rendering%20it%20ineffective%20in%20the%20field.%20Now%20he's%20standing%20up%20another%20brigade%2C%20one%20that%20will%20operate%20directly%20under%20the%20aegis%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces.%20As%20yet%20unnamed%2C%20the%20new%20unit%20will%20be%20trained%20and%20advised%20by%20military%20veterans%20from%20America%2C%20Canada%2C%20Great%20Britain%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20Australia.%20The%20goal%2C%20Sokolov%20says%2C%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bexecute%20complex%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20opposed%20to%20mere%20hit-and-run%20raids.%20The%20unit's%20Russian%20participants%20will%20be%20true%20soldiers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20once%20their%20reputation%20for%20professionalism%20and%20bravery%20is%20established%2C%20he%20is%20confident%2C%20the%20new%20brigade%20will%20become%20a%20magnet%20for%20fresh%20batches%20of%20volunteers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20government%20in%20Kyiv%20considers%20the%20number%20of%20Russian%20volunteers%20on%20the%20ground%20a%20state%20secret.%20Unsubstantiated%20estimates%20among%20anti-Putin%20militants%20range%20as%20high%20as%2010%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tiny%20band%20of%20brothers%2C%20at%20best%2C%20compared%20with%20the%20450%2C000%20in%20Putin's%20armed%20forces%20in%20Ukraine%20now.%20Whatever%20the%20precise%20count%2C%20every%20volunteer%20matters.%20Kyiv%20is%20struggling%20to%20replenish%20the%20ranks%20of%20its%20armed%20forces%2C%20as%20the%20war%20has%20already%20claimed%20the%20lives%20of%20at%20least%2031%2C000%20Ukrainian%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20volunteers%20are%20not%20a%20meaningful%20military%20threat%20to%20the%20Russian%20homeland%2C%20but%20their%20symbolic%20value%20is%20high.%20In%20March%2C%20as%20Russia%20was%20holding%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2024%2F03%2F18%2Fputin-wins-reelection-russia-president-victory-speech%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esham%20presidential%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dozens%20of%20Russian%20fighters%20engaged%20Putin's%20forces%20in%20an%20assault%20aimed%20at%20the%20border%20regions%20of%20Belgorod%20and%20Kursk.%20The%20fighters%20claimed%20to%20have%20crossed%20the%20border%20into%20Russia%3B%20Putin's%20Defense%20Ministry%20insisted%20that%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Brepulsed%26quot%3B%20the%20attack%2C%20dealing%20out%20heavy%20casualties.%20Whatever%20the%20case%2C%20the%20specter%20of%20Russians%20taking%20up%20arms%20against%20Russia%20is%20not%20an%20image%20that%20Putin%20wants%20to%20see%20spread%20to%20the%20populace%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20impossible%20to%20gauge%20how%20much%20of%20an%20existential%20threat%2C%20if%20any%2C%20Russia's%20new%20revolutionaries%20pose%20to%20Putin's%20rule.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20they%20present%2C%20at%20most%2C%20an%20embarrassment%2C%20a%20psychological%20rebuke%20to%20Putin.%20In%20the%20Russia%20that%20his%20propaganda%20wizards%20have%20fabricated%2C%20of%20patriotic%20citizens%20standing%20united%20against%20the%20malevolent%20West%20and%20NATO's%20puppet%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20these%20rebels%20are%20not%20supposed%20to%20exist%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20exactly%20Putin%20is%20to%20be%20overthrown%20is%20a%20question%2C%20I%20found%20in%20my%20conversations%20with%20the%20rebels%2C%20that%20eludes%20a%20ready%20answer.%20There%20is%20no%20master%20plan.%20For%20every%20Ammosov%2C%20convinced%20that%20sabotage%20of%20the%20economy%20is%20the%20key%2C%20there%20are%20others%20who%20believe%20that%20their%20example%2C%20of%20militant%20resistance%20to%20Putin's%20soldiers%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20can%20inspire%20fellow%20Russians%20back%20in%20the%20motherland%20to%20turn%20against%20the%20tsarlike%20ruler%20in%20the%20Kremlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Servicemen%20from%20the%20Siberian%20Battalion%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces%20International%20Legion%20are%20attending%20military%20exercises%20in%20the%20Kyiv%20region%2C%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d8a166289b805d1db43de3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Siberian%20Battalion%2C%20a%20brigade%20of%20Russians%20who%20fight%20alongside%20Ukrainians%2C%20training%20in%20April%202024.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20every%20revolution%2C%20in%20the%20early%20going%2C%20has%20been%20dismissed%20as%20inconsequential%2C%20from%20Lenin%20and%20Leon%20Trotsky%20in%20tsarist-Russia%20times%20to%20Mao%20Zedong%20in%20China%20and%20Fidel%20Castro%20in%20Cuba.%20Violent%20revolution%20requires%20herculean%20levels%20of%20organization%2C%20patience%2C%20and%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20succeed%2C%20revolution%20must%20also%20weather%20a%20storm%20of%20criticism%20from%20those%20who%20advocate%20change%20by%20more%20peaceful%20means.%20Outside%20Sokolov's%20circle%2C%20the%20new%20anti-Putin%20militants%20are%20scorned%20by%20many%20Russian%20political%20activists%20in%20exile%20who%20oppose%20violence%20both%20in%20principle%20and%20in%20practice.%20Any%20attempt%20at%20an%20armed%20insurrection%2C%20they%20warn%2C%20will%20ultimately%20backfire%2C%20alienating%20Russian%20citizens%20who%20might%20otherwise%20be%20sympathetic%20to%20the%20anti-Putin%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20think%20that%20the%20road%20to%20the%20victory%20of%20democracy%20lies%20through%20one%20group%20of%20Russians%20shooting%20at%20other%20Russians%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Boris%20Akunin%2C%20a%20popular%20Russian%20writer%20and%20a%20founder%20of%20True%20Russia%2C%20an%20anti-Putin%20group%20of%20exiles.%20%26quot%3BThis%20would%20never%20be%20understood%20and%20supported%20by%20the%20Russian%20people.%20I%20believe%20that%20the%20road%20to%20victory%20lies%20through%20motivating%20the%20mobilized%20Russian%20soldiers%20to%20revolt%20against%20the%20dictatorship.%20That's%20how%20revolutions%20happen.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20form%20of%20insurgency%20that%20was%20employed%20by%20the%20Bolsheviks%3A%20Win%20over%20the%20tsar's%20soldiers%2C%20and%20the%20tsar%20will%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevolutions%20also%20have%20a%20way%20of%20fracturing%20from%20within%2C%20as%20their%20leaders%20jockey%20for%20positions%20to%20exercise%20command%20once%20the%20despised%20regime%20is%20overthrown.%20One%20Russian%20revolutionary%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20is%20already%20claiming%20the%20mantle%20of%20leadership%20in%20a%20post-Putin%20Russia.%20Ilya%20Ponomarev%2C%20the%2049-year-old%20dissident%20who%20was%20nearly%20killed%20by%20a%20Russian%20drone%20strike%20in%20August%2C%20is%20a%20former%20tech%20entrepreneur%20who%20served%20in%20the%20Russian%20parliament.%20Today%2C%20he's%20the%20political%20head%20of%20the%20Freedom%20of%20Russia%20Legion%2C%20another%20anti-Putin%20volunteer%20brigade%20in%20Ukraine.%20And%20perhaps%20more%20importantly%2C%20he%20has%20cultivated%20a%20vibrant%20profile%20in%20Washington%2C%20where%20he%20has%20become%20a%20fixture%20of%20the%20Russian%20exile%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20in%20March%2C%20I%20met%20in%20Washington%20with%20Ponomarev%20and%20several%20figures%20in%20his%20retinue.%20We%20started%20with%20late-afternoon%20drinks%20at%20a%20hotel%20before%20shifting%20to%20more%20drinks%2C%20and%20pizza%2C%20at%20Ponomarev's%20ski-chalet-like%20home%20in%20Northern%20Virginia.%20As%20he%20drew%20on%20a%20flavored-tobacco%20water%20pipe%20and%20sipped%20from%20a%20bottle%20of%20Bold%20Rock%20Imperial%20Cider%2C%20Ponomarev%20extolled%20the%20prospects%20for%20a%20violent%20revolution%20in%20Russia%2C%20precipitated%20by%20the%20volunteer%20fighters%20in%20Ukraine.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20supported%20by%20the%20Russian%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20already%20have%20enough%20force%20to%20hold%20a%20certain%20ground%26quot%3B%20inside%20Russia.%20On%20my%20departure%2C%20he%20handed%20me%20an%20inscribed%20copy%20of%20his%202002%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BDoes%20Putin%20Have%20to%20Die%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20unlike%20Trotsky%2C%20Mao%2C%20and%20Castro%2C%20Ponomarev%20is%20not%20hunkered%20down%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20with%20his%20fellow%20insurgents.%20Instead%2C%20he%20spends%20part%20of%20his%20time%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20punctuated%20by%20frequent%20visits%20to%20various%20European%20capitals%20and%20his%20home%20outside%20Washington.%20A%20Russian%20fighter%20in%20the%20Freedom%20of%20Russia%20Legion%20stressed%20to%20me%20that%20Ponomarev%20does%20not%20speak%20for%20those%20actively%20involved%20in%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20claims%20leadership%20of%20a%20political%20group%2C%20the%20Congress%20of%20People's%20Deputies%2C%20that%20advocates%20for%20violent%20resistance%20to%20the%20Kremlin.%20During%20our%20meeting%20in%20Washington%2C%20Ponomarev%20introduced%20me%20to%20Alexei%20Sobchenko%2C%20a%20former%20State%20Department%20translator%20who%20now%20serves%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20agent%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20congress.%20Sobchenko's%20registration%20papers%2C%20filed%20with%20the%20Justice%20Department%20in%20October%2C%20cite%20an%20address%20in%20Warsaw%20for%20the%20congress.%20But%20the%20group%20has%20no%20actual%20office%20there%2C%20as%20I%20discovered%20on%20my%20trip%20to%20Poland%3B%20the%20address%20led%20me%20to%20a%20residence%20in%20a%20leafy%20suburb%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221953%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20of%20Ilya%20Ponomarev%20unhurt%20(on%20left)%2C%20hurt%20after%20protest%20(on%20right).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d72e3b1d8d2deb96b82ccf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221465%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIlya%20Ponomarev%2C%20a%20former%20tech%20entrepreneur%20who%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20Russian%20drone%20strike%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20has%20cultivated%20a%20vibrant%20profile%20in%20Washington%20as%20the%20political%20head%20of%20the%20Freedom%20of%20Russia%20Legion.%3Cp%3ESergei%20Chuzavkov%2F%20AP%20Images%3B%20Courtesy%20of%20Ilya%20Ponomarev%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPonomarev%20told%20me%20the%20home%20in%20Warsaw%20is%20just%20the%20group's%20%26quot%3Blegal%20address.%26quot%3B%20And%20it's%20true%20that%20the%20congress%20has%20organized%20several%20high-profile%20events%20in%20Warsaw%2C%20including%20a%20March%20forum%20that%20was%20attended%20by%20Micha%C5%82%20Kami%C5%84ski%2C%20the%20deputy%20speaker%20of%20the%20Polish%20Senate.%20Ponomarev%20told%20participants%20at%20the%20forum%20that%20the%20congress%20is%20%26quot%3Bformulating%20alternative%20governing%20bodies%20in%20Russia%26quot%3B%20to%20take%20over%20after%20Putin's%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20leaders%20of%20the%20insurgency%20dismiss%20such%20theatrics.%20In%20Warsaw%2C%20Sokolov%20and%20his%20associates%20all%20told%20me%20they%20consider%20Ponomarev%20a%20charlatan.%20Kosinova%2C%20whose%20son%20is%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20likened%20Ponomarev%20to%20Pavel%20Ivanovich%20Chichikov%2C%20the%20schemer%20in%20Nikolai%20Gogol's%20novel%20%26quot%3BDead%20Souls%26quot%3B%20who%20%26quot%3Bpurchases%26quot%3B%20deceased%20male%20serfs%20to%20create%20a%20facade%20of%20wealth.%20That's%20quite%20a%20gibe.%20For%20an%20American%20equivalent%2C%20think%20of%20a%20flimflam-man%20compound%20of%20P.T.%20Barnum%2C%20Bernie%20%26quot%3BPonzi%20Scheme%26quot%3B%20Madoff%2C%20and%20Donald%20%26quot%3BTrump%20University%26quot%3B%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPonomarev%20is%20acutely%20aware%20of%20the%20barbs.%20In%20Lviv%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20at%20a%20recent%20summit%20of%20prominent%20Russian%20exiles%20supporting%20the%20violent%20resistance%20against%20Putin%2C%20he%20was%20lambasted%20by%20Leonid%20Nevzlin%2C%20a%20rich%20former%20business%20partner%20of%20the%20onetime%20oil%20baron%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-oligarchs-putins-agents-mikhail-khodorkovsky-says-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMikhail%20Khodorkovsky%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nevzlin%2C%20by%20Ponomarev's%20account%2C%20expressed%20distrust%20of%20the%20Freedom%20of%20Russia%20Legion%20and%20accused%20Ponomarev%20of%20wanting%20to%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bnew%20Navalny.%26quot%3B%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-life-career-of-putin-critic-alexei-navalny-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENavalny%20himself%3C%2Fa%3E%20never%20supported%20armed%20resistance%20to%20Putin.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legion's%20political%20leader%20considers%20the%20attack%20a%20badge%20of%20honor.%20%26quot%3BNevzlin%20is%20just%20an%20old%2C%20bored%20man.%20He%20is%20jealous%20of%20all%20rising%20stars%2C%26quot%3B%20Ponomarev%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BMy%20position%20is%20simple.%20There%20are%20no%20enemies%20in%20the%20opposition.%20We%20can%20debate%20the%20tactics%2C%20but%20we%20should%20not%20fight%20each%20other.%20Let%20the%20thousand%20flowers%20bloom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20small%20and%20insular%20nature%20of%20the%20anti-Putin%20opposition%2C%20its%20internal%20disagreements%20have%20the%20character%20of%20family%20squabbles%20of%20a%20certain%20intense%20character.%20A%20parallel%2C%20perhaps%2C%20is%20to%20the%20American%2018th-century%20revolutionaries%20who%20all%20aimed%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20King%20George%20III%20but%20were%20riven%20by%20personal%20enmities%20and%20tactical%20disputes.%20So%2C%20too%2C%20the%20leading%20figures%20in%20the%20Russian%20opposition%20to%20Putin%20are%20all%20familiar%20with%20each%20other%20from%20way%20back.%20Ponomarev%20himself%2C%20years%20ago%2C%20worked%20as%20a%20deputy%20at%20Yukos%2C%20the%20Russian%20oil%20conglomerate%20once%20presided%20over%20by%20Khodorkovsky.%20From%20his%20base%20in%20London%2C%20Khodorkovsky%20now%20funds%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20anti-Kremlin%20political%20activities%20and%20serves%20as%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20the%20Russian%20Anti-War%20Committee.%20Through%20an%20aide%2C%20Khodorkovsky%20told%20me%20that%20the%20committee%20%26quot%3Bhas%20decided%20that%20we%20shall%20not%20cooperate%20with%20Ilya%20Ponomarev%20because%20we%20are%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20range%20of%20nonviolent%20ways%20of%20resistance%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20the%20committee%20cannot%20support%20armed%20resistance.%26quot%3B%20The%20aide%20added%20that%20Khodorkovsky%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20an%20individual%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20involved%26quot%3B%20in%20any%20way%20with%20the%20anti-Putin%20military%20insurgency%20being%20mounted%20by%20his%20fellow%20Russians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20members%20of%20the%20Anti-War%20Committee%20have%20embraced%20the%20ongoing%20Russian%20war%20on%20Putin.%20Among%20them%20is%20Garry%20Kasparov%2C%20the%20former%20world%20chess%20champion%20turned%20political%20activist%20who%20is%20a%20declared%20supporter%20of%20the%20Russian%20volunteers%20in%20Ukraine.%20Another%20committee%20member%20told%20me%20he%20would%20be%20assassinated%20if%20Putin's%20operatives%20knew%20how%20active%20he%20is%20in%20the%20military%20effort%20to%20stop%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20The%20committee%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20is%20splintering%20on%20the%20core%2C%20inescapable%20question%20of%20the%20necessity%20of%20violence%20to%20effect%20change%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20win%20political%20support%20for%20the%20militants'%20cause%20in%20Washington%2C%20Ponomarev%2C%20in%20March%2C%20told%20me%20he%20was%20establishing%20a%20base%20of%20lobbying%20and%20public-relations%20operations%20at%20a%20three-story%20red-brick%20property%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%2C%20a%20few%20blocks%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20But%20the%20next%20day%2C%20when%20I%20dropped%20by%20the%20address%2C%20I%20found%20a%20real-estate%20agency's%20sign%20out%20front.%20Months%20later%2C%20there%20was%20still%20no%20record%20of%20a%20transaction.%20%26quot%3BThe%20property%20is%20under%20contract%20with%20us%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20is%20not%20yet%20closed%2C%26quot%3B%20Ponomarev%20assured%20me.%20Who%2C%20I%20asked%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bus%26quot%3B%3F%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20it%20is%20with%20me%20personally%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20replied.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20final%20deal%20would%20be%20some%20neutral%20NGO%2C%20so%20the%20house%20would%20be%20a%20joint%20effort%20by%20different%20opposition%20groups.%26quot%3B%20He%20declines%20to%20say%20who%20is%20paying%20for%20the%20property%2C%20the%20value%20of%20which%20Zillow%20estimates%20is%20%242.24%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20target%20of%20Ponomarev's%20lobbying%20efforts%20is%20Rep.%20Brian%20Fitzpatrick%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20a%20former%20FBI%20special%20agent%20who%20sits%20on%20the%20House%20Permanent%20Select%20Committee%20on%20Intelligence%20and%20is%20a%20leading%20supporter%20of%20US%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine.%20Ponomarev%20says%20the%20anti-Putin%20resistance%20has%20support%20from%20elected%20officials%20in%20both%20the%20House%20and%20the%20Senate%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20all%20very%20sensitive%2C%20and%20many%20people%20even%20have%20to%20deny%20our%20acquaintance.%26quot%3B%20Fitzpatrick's%20office%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Ponomarev%20associate%20suggested%20I%20imagine%20%26quot%3BCharlie%20Wilson's%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20the%202007%20film%20about%20the%20flamboyant%20congressman%20from%20Texas%2C%20played%20by%20Tom%20Hanks%2C%20who%20heroically%20secured%20funding%20for%20the%20CIA%20to%20arm%20the%20mujahideen%20resistance%20to%20Soviet%20forces%20in%20Afghanistan.%20To%20stay%20with%20the%20movie%20parallel%2C%20it%20seems%20Ponomarev%20is%20searching%2C%20too%2C%20for%20a%20CIA%20officer%20to%20back%20the%20rebellion%20cause%2C%20a%20role%20played%20in%20the%20film%20by%20Philip%20Seymour%20Hoffman.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20good%20officers%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20CIA%2C%20Ponomarev%20told%20me%2C%20who%20%26quot%3Bsympathize%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20anti-Putin%20insurgency.%20But%20when%20I%20asked%20the%20CIA%20for%20comment%2C%20the%20agency%20comes%20as%20close%20to%20a%20full%20denial%20of%20involvement%20as%20one%20can%20imagine%20it%20making.%20%26quot%3BConsistent%20with%20US%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20CIA%20works%20closely%20with%20the%20Ukrainian%20Security%20Services%2C%20and%20not%20ad%20hoc%20groups%20of%20volunteers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Fried%2C%20a%20former%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Poland%2C%20rejects%20the%20notion%20that%20William%20Burns%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20CIA%2C%20%26quot%3Bwould%20allow%20any%20support%26quot%3B%20for%20Russians%20fighting%20Putin.%20The%20agency%20wouldn't%20risk%20being%20associated%20with%20them%2C%20Fried%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bin%20case%20they%20do%20something%20you%20don't%20like.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20not%20actively%20objecting%20to%20Kyiv's%20standing%20up%20of%20the%20anti-Putin%20Russian-volunteer%20units.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20going%20out%20of%20our%20way%20to%20tell%20the%20Ukrainians%20to%20cut%20them%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Fried%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhoever%20emerges%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20violent%20resistance%2C%20it%20has%20attracted%20backing%20from%20some%20seemingly%20improbable%20figures.%20Supporters%20include%20Evgenia%20Chirikova%2C%20a%20Russian%20environmental%20activist%20who%20won%20global%20acclaim%20for%20her%20efforts%20to%20protect%20an%20old-growth%20forest%20outside%20Moscow.%20%26quot%3BThis%20violence%20started%20with%20Putin%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me%20from%20her%20base%20in%20Tallinn%2C%20Estonia.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20organize%20an%20equal%20answer.%26quot%3B%20Another%20avowed%20militant%20is%20Andrey%20Volna%2C%20a%20renowned%20trauma%20surgeon%20in%20his%20early%2060s%20who%20once%20occupied%20a%20prestigious%20medical%20post%20in%20Moscow.%20%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20I%20am%20an%20extremely%20peaceful%20guy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20from%20Tallinn.%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20we%20need%20military%20force%20to%20change%20the%20fascist%2C%20dictatorial%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20belief%2C%20even%20among%20former%20advocates%20of%20non-violence%2C%20that%20Putin%20can%20be%20deposed%20only%20by%20an%20armed%20insurrection%2C%20is%20what%20Russia's%20new%20revolutionaries%20are%20counting%20on.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20act%20as%20a%20vanguard%20%E2%80%94%20or%20influencers%2C%20in%20the%20modern%20parlance%20%E2%80%94%20to%20set%20an%20example%20for%20their%20fellow%20Russians.%20By%20word%20and%20deed%2C%20they%20aim%20to%20create%20a%20flock%20of%20followers%20capable%20of%20toppling%20a%20tyrant.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20our%20conversations%20in%20Warsaw%2C%20when%20I%20ask%20Ammosov%20whether%20it's%20really%20possible%20to%20overthrow%20Putin%2C%20he%20points%20not%20to%20the%20future%20but%20to%20the%20country's%20not-so-distant%20past.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Russian%20empire%20collapsed%20twice%20in%20the%2020th%20century%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20observes%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Bolshevik%20Revolution%20in%201917%20and%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20USSR%20in%201991.%20And%20both%20times%2C%20he%20notes%2C%20the%20uprising%20happened%20suddenly%2C%20seemingly%20without%20warning.%20Russians%20know%20from%20long%20and%20bitter%20experience%20that%20when%20the%20last%20resort%20comes%20to%20look%20like%20the%20only%20resort%2C%20anything%20is%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fpaul-starobin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EPaul%20Starobin%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BPutin's%20Exiles%3A%20Their%20Fight%20for%20a%20Better%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-plot-russian-exiles-overthrow-vladimir-putin-ukraine-war-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725875342000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d234db43b5e59d16b742ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-plot-russian-exiles-overthrow-vladimir-putin-ukraine-war-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20growing%20army%20of%20Russian%20expats%20want%20to%20take%20back%20Russia.%20Can%20they%20succeed%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22paul.starobin%40gmail.com%20(Paul%20Starobin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-plot-russian-exiles-overthrow-vladimir-putin-ukraine-war-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20you%20work%20from%20home%20it's%20tempting%20to%20skip%20your%20lunch%20break.%20Workplace%20experts%20say%20it%20co