%20a%20lunch%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F8cd66c20-de93-4765-9f6a-3cce51e97021%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Financial%20Times'%20Isabel%20Berwick%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20spoke%20to%20Professor%20Nick%20Bloom%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20who%20said%20that%20workers%20in%20the%20office%20are%20still%20taking%20lunch%20breaks%2C%20whereas%20for%20their%20colleagues%20who%20work%20from%20home%2C%20there%20is%20generally%20a%20smaller%20dip%2C%20or%20no%20dip%20at%20all%2C%20in%20activity%20around%20lunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22045ad50d-d808-49e1-b7cc-10f5f53a720d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Multi-tasking'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Mark%20Mortensen%2C%20who%20teaches%20MBA%2C%20EMBA%2C%20and%20PhD%20students%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20INSEAD%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20goal%20of%20a%20lunch%20break%20is%20to%20give%20you%20a%20change%20of%20pace%20and%20enough%20time%20to%20immerse%20yourself%20in%20whatever%20work%20task%20is%20to%20be%20done%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-manager-lunch-every-day-month-better-work-life-balance-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estill%20doing%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20lunch%20break%2C%26quot%3B%20Mortensen%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20sitting%20in%20front%20of%20a%20laptop%2C%20trying%20to%20do%20your%20job%20and%20eat%20a%20meal%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bmulti-tasking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20ideally%2C%20employees%20should%20take%20a%20complete%20break%20during%20this%20time%20to%20recharge.%20Mortensen%20advised%20against%20checking%20incoming%20messages%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-successful-people-do-during-their-lunch-break-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eengaging%20in%20certain%20