tabolism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverworking%20and%20burnout%20from%20not%20taking%20a%20proper%20break%20can%20also%20contribute%20to%20mental%20health%20issues%2C%20Tavis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPsychologically%2C%20it's%20really%20important%2C%20especially%20if%20your%20work%20is%20intense%20and%20if%20you%20want%20to%20get%20back%20and%20stay%20focused%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20outlining%20that%20well-rested%20employees%20are%20more%20productive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239649776-9243-4be3-839d-efe7251bdc41%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20could%20be%20owed%20overtime%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJanice%20DiRose%2C%20a%20labor%20and%20employment%20attorney%20and%20human%20resources%20consultant%20based%20in%20Florida%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20a%20company%20could%20get%20into%20legal%20trouble%20if%20its%20staff%20works%20during%20lunchtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20employees%20who%20are%20eligible%20for%20overtime%20are%20eating%20at%20their%20desks%20instead%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-from-home-best-habit-taking-a-lunch-break-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaking%20time%20off%20for%20lunch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20is%20very%20concerning%20from%20an%20HR%20compliance%20standpoint%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20sitting%20at%20your%20desk%20and%20you're%20looking%20at%20your%20email%20and%20occasionally%20answering%2C%20you%20are%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20DiRose%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20in%20the%20US%2C%20that%20means%20you%20need%20to%20get%20paid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20that%20under%20the%20Fair%20Labor%20Standards%20Act%20of%201938%2C%20meal%20times%20are%20only%20considered%20breaks%20if%20workers%20are%20not%20engaged%20in%20the%20duties%20of%20their%20jobs.%20So%2C%20if%20they%20work%20during%20lunch%2C%20they're%20owed%20overtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20an%20employer%2C%20you%20can't%20just%20allow%20your%20entire%20workforce%20to%20sit%20at%20a%20desk%20and%20get%20paid%20for%20lunch%2C%26quot%3B%20DiRose%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e820ad92-20bc-4ab7-9ed6-6d244d016b93%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmployers%20need%20to%20do%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDiRose%20said%20the%20best%20preventive%20measure%20to%20ensure%20employees%20are%20taking%20breaks%20is%20more%20training.%20Otherwise%2C%20they%20might%20adopt%20bad%20habits%20from%20previous%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETavis%20said%20that%20for%20hybrid%20setups%2C%20managers%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20encourage%20staff%20to%20take%20lunch%20on%20in-office%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20need%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20intentional%20around%20those%20moments%20that%20matter%20in%20the%20building%2C%20that%20social%20fabric%20of%20the%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-lunch-experts-broken-not-take-breaks-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725874998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66db02a65444ffafa7630f6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-lunch-experts-broken-not-take-breaks-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Remote%20workers%20are%20skipping%20lunch%2C%20often%20substituting%20it%20for%20snacking%20throughout%20the%20day.%20This%20can%20be%20bad%20for%20wellbeing%20and%20impact%20productivity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nredmond%40insider.com%20(Nora%20Redmond)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-lunch-experts-broken-not-take-breaks-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20cult%20of%20Nvidia%20is%20getting%20really%20weird%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20o