unicating%20with%20your%20employer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Rooney%20had%20worked%20at%20Twitter%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20director%20of%20%26quot%3Bsource%20to%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20procurement%20role%2C%20in%20Twitter's%20European%20headquarters%20in%20Dublin%20when%20Elon%20Musk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-reach-agreement-to-close-acquisition-deal-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%20the%20social%20media%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2444%20billion%20in%20October%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20weeks%20of%20taking%20over%20Twitter%2C%20Musk%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-musks-midnight-email-telling-twitter-staff-work-long-hours-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow-infamous%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20entire%20workforce%2C%20asking%20them%20to%20commit%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20hardcore%26quot%3B%20work%20schedule%20or%20resign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20will%20mean%20working%20long%20hours%20at%20high%20intensity.%20Only%20exceptional%20performance%20will%20constitute%20a%20passing%20grade%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20billionaire%20wrote%20in%20the%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20didn't%20click%20yes%20on%20a%20link%20in%20the%20email%20to%20%26quot%3Bbe%20part%20of%20the%20new%20Twitter%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20next%20day%20would%20receive%20three%20months'%20severance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERooney%20fell%20into%20that%20group.%20But%20rather%20than%20leaving%20quietly%2C%20he%20brought%20a%20case%20to%20Ireland's%20Workplace%20Relations%20Commission%20(WRC)%2C%20claiming%20unfair%20dismissal.%20He%20won%20and%20was%20awarded%20around%20%24600%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%20released%20documents%20detail%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.workplacerelations.ie%2Fen%2Fcases%2F2024%2Faugust%2Fadj-00044246.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20WRC's%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20revealing%20new%20details%20about%20Rooney's%20case%20and%20Twitter's%20HR%20practices%20under%20Musk's%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERooney%20saw%20the%20email%20but%20did%20not%20respond.%20Three%20days%20later%2C%20he%20received%20a%20second%20email%20from%20HR%20acknowledging%20his%20%26quot%3Bdecision%20to%20resign%20and%20accept%20the%20voluntary%20separation%20offer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20no%20time%20have%20I%20indicated%20to%20Twitter%20that%20I%20am%20resigning%20my%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20replied%2C%20a%20week%20later%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WRC's%20report.%20The%20company%20told%20him%20that%20not%20clicking%20yes%20was%20%26quot%3Btreated%20as%20you%20having%20served%20notice%20to%20resign%20your%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d74eadbb-35ff-4f38-a203-fd146f6031a8%5C%22%3EResignation%20by%20omission%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20not%20seem%20like%20common%20practice%20to%20terminate%20an%20employee%20without%20speaking%20to%20them%2C%20but%20no-show%20resignations%20aren't%20unheard%20of%2C%20said%20Robyn%20Hopper%2C%20an%20HR%20knowledge%20advisor%20at%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%20(SHRM).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployee%20handbooks%20explain%20when%20termination%20may%20be%20considered%20a%20voluntary%20resignation.%20The%20issue%20is%20that%20many%20employees%20tend%20not%20to%20read%20company%20policies%20or%20handbooks%20until%20it's%20too%20late%2C%20said%20Stefanie%20Camfield%2C%20director%20of%20HR%20at%20Engage%20PEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Workers%20install%20lighting%20on%20an%20%26quot%3BX%26quot%3B%20sign%20atop%20the%20downtown%20San%20Francisco%20building%20that%20housed%20what%20was%20formally%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20now%20rebranded%20X%20by%20owner%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20Friday%2C%20July%2028%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6584ad17a79e5746976c8275%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwitter%20was%20rebranded%20X%2C%20another%20change%20introduced%20by%20its%20new%20owner%20Elon%20Musk.%20%3Cp%3ENoah%20Berger%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECamfield%20said%20the%20other%20factor%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20is%20that%20many%20US%20companies%20do%20not%20offer%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-consider-before-you-sign-severance-contract-labor-lawyer-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewritten%20employment%20contract%20to%20workers%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20position%20in%20a%20company%20is%20mostly%20%26quot%3Bat-will.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt-will%20means%20an%20employer%20or%20the%20employee%20can%20end%20the%20employment%20relationship%20for%20any%20reason%20or%20no%20reason%2C%20so%20long%20as%20it's%20not%20unlawful%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20anything%20is%20disputed%2C%20the%20courts%20generally%20place%20the%20employee%20in%20a%20position%20of%20less%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20an%20employer%20can%20terminate%20an%20employee%20without%20notice%20if%20they%20fail%20to%20show%20up%20for%20work.%20They%20assume%20the%20employee%20has%20decided%20to%20resign%20and%20just%20hasn't%20told%20them%20yet%2C%20Camfield%20said.%20This%20is%20known%20as%20job%20abandonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20long%20the%20employee%20has%20depends%2C%20but%20most%20companies%20that%20Camfield%20works%20with%20set%20a%20three%20day%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233637c09-a5a4-40d8-a04c-79ff20f85ebb%5C%22%3ECommunication%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECamfield%20said%20Twitter's%20handling%20of%20the%20situation%20was%20hampered%20by%20unclear%20communication%20and%20informal%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20employee%20wasn't%20really%20given%20clear%20terms%20on%20the%20changes%20to%20the%20terms%20of%20their%20employment.%20They%20were%20just%20told%20Twitter%202.0%2C%20that's%20not%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20stood%20out%20to%20me%20is%20that%20there's%20a%20question%20about%20whether%20the%20statement%20that%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20employee%20could%20be%20construed%20as%20the%20employee%20resigning%20by%20not%20checking%20yes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Camfied.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20anything%20that%20actually%20evidences%20that%20the%20employee%20resigned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20thought%20that%20the%20employee%20could%20have%20responded%20in%20some%20manner%20on%20the%20day%2C%20even%20if%20they%20did%20not%20agree%20with%20what%20was%20being%20presented%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnding%20an%20employment%20relationship%20generally%20deserves%20face-to-face%20or%20at%20least%20personalized%20conversations%2C%20she%20said.%20But%20phone%20calls%20are%20often%20time-consuming%20and%20need%20to%20be%20scheduled.%20Particularly%20for%20a%20large%20workforce%2C%20it's%20just%20not%20feasible%20to%20individually%20call%20all%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHopper%20pointed%20out%20that%20sometimes%20HR%20has%20their%20hands%20tied%20and%20is%20acting%20on%20orders%20from%20upper%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20employers%20have%20a%20requirement%20that%20if%20an%20employee%20is%20resigning%2C%20and%20it%20is%20written%20as%20an%20email%20or%20text%2C%20they%20will%20call%20an%20employee%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20what%20was%20received%20is%20legitimate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20is%20no%20law%20that%20I%20am%20aware%20of%20that%20states%20that%20an%20employee%20or%20employer%20cannot%20use%20email%20or%20other%20communication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20and%20remote%20work%20has%20also%20created%20a%20new%20challenge%20for%20HR%20professionals%2C%20particularly%20with%20employees%20spread%20across%20regions%20with%20different%20regulations%2C%20Hopper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22213b19d3-ce53-48a1-960b-84dff8fd7dc7%5C%22%3EYour%20Slack%20messages%20aren't%20private%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WRC%20decision%20report%20shows%20that%20on%20the%20day%20Rooney%20received%20Musk's%20email%2C%20he%20messaged%20a%20colleague%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmajor-companies-using-ai-to-track-slack-messages-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESlack%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BHey%20%E2%80%93%20wanted%20to%20let%20you%20know%20im%20going.%20I%20need%20to%20step%20away%20for%20my%20own%20sake.%20I'm%20deeply%20troubled%20by%20whats%20going%20on%20here%20these%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20message%2C%20he%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BIv%20made%20the%20decision%20not%20to%20press%20the%20yes%20button%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20drop%20in%20a%20goodbye%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter%20used%20these%20messages%20and%20others%20as%20evidence%20that%20he%20intended%20to%20leave%20the%20company.%20The%20WRC%20found%20the%20slack%20messages%20had%20%26quot%3Bno%20relevance%20to%20the%20question%20as%20to%20what%20brought%20about%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20Complainant's%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Rooney%20won%20his%20case%2C%20experts%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20should%20serve%20as%20a%20reminder%20to%20all%20employees%20about%20the%20risks%20of%20using%20internal%20messaging%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221452%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22New%20Slack%20redesign%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d1d243cc84b4dfaff8961%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221042%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESlack%20is%20a%20great%20tool%20for%20communication%20in%20the%20hybrid%20world%2C%20said%20Camfield.%3Cp%3ESlack%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20often%20have%20the%20right%20to%20monitor%20and%20preserve%20data%20on%20Slack.%20They%20primarily%20use%20it%20to%20ensure%20company%20policies%20are%20being%20followed%2C%20said%20Camfield%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20used%20however%20they%20see%20fit%20%E2%80%94%20including%20as%20evidence%20in%20a%20lawsuit%2C%20as%20Twitter%20did%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20necessarily%20a%20bad%20thing%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20messaging%20tends%20to%20encourage%20employees%20to%20talk%20more%20frequently%20and%20more%20casually.%20And%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20inappropriate%20conversations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlack%20messages%20could%20just%20as%20easily%20be%20used%20as%20evidence%20in%20a%20sexual%20harassment%20case%2C%20Camfield%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlack%20is%20still%20a%20great%20tool%20for%20keeping%20teams%20connected%20in%20the%20age%20of%20hybrid%20work.%20However%2C%20employers%20need%20to%20train%20employees%20to%20understand%20that%20company%20policies%20extend%20to%20Slack%20and%20that%20their%20information%20is%20not%20private%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-unfair-dismissal-case-learnings-for-workers-employers-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725873933000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d9befaa0ff598b26648e7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-unfair-dismissal-case-learnings-for-workers-employers-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Twitter%20employee%20won%20%24600K%20for%20unfair%20dismissal%20after%20not%20responding%20to%20Musk's%20%26quot%3Bhardcore%26quot%3B%20work%20email.%20These%20are%20the%20lessons%20to%20learn%20from%20this%20case.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40insider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-unfair-dismissal-case-learnings-for-workers-employers-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22tit