ile%20phone%20screen.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668424da1aace5b3ada3a445%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221411%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20faces%20a%20landmark%20antitrust%20trial%20over%20its%20alleged%20digital%20ad%20market%20monopoly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20DOJ%20and%2017%20states%20allege%20Google%20used%20acquisitions%20and%20ad%20auction%20tactics%20illegally.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20breakup%20could%20reshape%20the%20%24691%20billion%20online%20ad%20market%2C%20boosting%20rivals%20like%20The%20Trade%20Desk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20executives%20and%20lawyers%20are%20headed%20to%20the%20Eastern%20District%20of%20Virginia%20Courthouse%20on%20Monday%20to%20face%20a%20landmark%20antitrust%20trial%20that%20could%20result%20in%20the%20breakup%20of%20its%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20outcome%20would%20be%20a%20boon%20for%20Google's%20adtech%20rivals%20but%20wouldn't%20necessarily%20provide%20an%20instant%20panacea%20for%20the%20publishers%20and%20advertisers%20that%20have%20come%20to%20depend%20on%20its%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%2C%20brought%20by%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20and%2017%20state%20attorneys%20general%2C%20alleges%20that%20Google%20used%20acquisitions%20and%20anticompetitive%20ad%20auction%20tactics%20to%20build%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20of%20the%20digital%20ad%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20is%20focused%20on%20the%20open%20web%20display%20ad%20market%20and%20the%20tools%20that%20power%20the%20ad%20auctions%20that%20happen%20in%20the%20milliseconds%20it%20takes%20for%20a%20webpage%20to%20load.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20owns%20an%20ad%20server%20that%20publishers%20use%20to%20manage%20their%20ad%20inventory%2C%20buying%20tools%20that%20advertisers%20use%20to%20purchase%20ads%2C%20and%20an%20ad%20exchange%20that%20connects%20the%20two.%20It%20owns%20the%20most%20popular%20of%20all%20three%20technologies%2C%20which%20the%20DOJ%20alleges%20helped%20the%20company%20impede%20rivals%2C%20inflate%20advertising%20costs%2C%20and%20reduce%20revenue%20for%20publishers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20is%20set%20to%20last%20multiple%20weeks%2C%20and%20Google%20will%20likely%20appeal%20if%20the%20judge%20doesn't%20rule%20in%20its%20favor.%20That%20means%20it%20could%20be%20months%20before%20the%20real%20ramifications%20of%20the%20case%20are%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20case%20is%20being%20closely%20watched%20by%20all%20members%20of%20the%20online%20ad%20ecosystem%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchart-na1.emarketer.com%2F265167%2Fdigital-ad-spending-worldwide-2022-2027-billions-change-of-total-ad-spending%23_gl%3D1*i6ho3e*_gcl_au*MjM0MjQ1ODQ0LjE3MjI5NDExNzUuMTI1NDc4NTAuMTcyMjk0MTE3Ni4xNzIyOTQxMTc4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24691%20billion%20in%20spending%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20DOJ%20and%20the%20states%20are%20seeking%20a%20breakup%20of%20Google's%20adtech%20business.%20Such%20a%20move%20would%20not%20only%20transform%20the%20online%20advertising%20landscape.%20It%20would%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bbiggest%20forced%20corporate%20shake-up%20since%20Microsoft%20unbundled%20the%20Internet%20Explorer%20browser%20in%202000%2C%26quot%3B%20Macquarie%20media%20tech%20analyst%20Tim%20Nollen%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20research%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20interviewed%20analysts%2C%20legal%20experts%2C%20and%20adtech%20insiders%20to%20explore%20how%20the%20industry%20would%20shape%20up%20if%20Google%20is%20declawed.%20Google%20on%20Sunday%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Foutreach-initiatives%2Fpublic-policy%2Fgoogle-ad-tech-sept-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20said%20it%20intends%20to%20show%20in%20court%20how%20advertisers%20and%20publishers%20choose%20to%20use%20its%20adtech%20because%20it%20%26quot%3Bsimple%2C%20affordable%2C%20and%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d9ba6873-391d-40b5-ab40-742d45033c22%5C%22%3EA%20Google%20breakup%20would%20be%20a%20major%20boost%20for%20rival%20adtech%20firms%20like%20The%20Trade%20Desk%20and%20Magnite%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20find%20an%20adtech%20company%20that%20isn't%20gunning%20for%20Google%20to%20lose%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ%20wants%20the%20judge%20to%20rule%20that%20Google%20needs%20to%20separate%20its%20publisher%20adtech%20%E2%80%94%20the%20DoubleClick%20for%20Publishers%20ad%20server%20and%20its%20Google%20AdExchange%20%E2%80%94%20from%20its%20advertiser%20adtech%2C%20namely%20its%20Google%20Ads%20and%20Display%20%26amp%3B%20Video%20360%20ad-buying%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221276%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google's%20ad%20tech%20stack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d73157289b805d1db399e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20goes%20that%20by%20owning%20the%20entire%20adtech%20stack%2C%20Google%20has%20access%20to%20a%20huge%20pool%20of%20ad%20inventory%20that%20it%20can%20tie%20to%20demand%20on%20its%20ad-buying%20platforms.%20That%20setup%20means%20most%20publishers%20select%20Google%20as%20their%20ad%20server%2C%20the%20complaint%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20Google%20has%20troves%20of%20user%20data%20from%20its%20logged-in%20users%20on%20platforms%20like%20Chrome%20and%20Gmail.%20Combined%2C%20that%20gives%20Google%20wide%20visibility%20across%20the%20entire%20auction%20process%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20refine%20its%20bids%20accordingly%2C%20and%20a%20way%20to%20self-preference%20its%20own%20ad%20inventory%20tech%2C%20the%20complaint%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20industry%20experts%20think%20that%20untethering%20Google's%20supply%20and%20demand%20side%20would%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20for%20competing%20tech%20companies%20with%20big%20advertising%20businesses%2C%20such%20as%20Meta%20and%20Amazon%2C%20as%20well%20as%20pureplay%20adtech%20firms.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20could%20boost%20innovation%20in%20the%20space%2C%20reducing%20costs%20for%20advertisers%20and%20increasing%20revenue%20for%20publishers%2C%20some%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BDemand-side%20platforms%5D%20like%20The%20Trade%20Desk%2C%20%5Bsupply-side%20platforms%5D%20like%20Magnite%20and%20PubMatic%2C%20specialist%20ad%20tech%20services%20like%20Criteo%2C%20and%20companies%20supporting%20alternative%20IDs%20and%20data%20collaboration%20like%20LiveRamp%2C%20all%20should%20see%20a%20better%20competitive%20landscape%20without%20the%20heavy%20hands%20of%20Google%20scooping%20up%20so%20much%20of%20the%20business%20itself%2C%20and%20for%20its%20own%20purposes%20(YouTube)%2C%26quot%3B%20Macquarie's%20Nollen%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20research%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20a%20divestiture%20could%20encourage%20more%20transparency%20and%20traceability%20of%20data%20flows%20within%20the%20online%20ad%20ecosystem%2C%20Elettra%20Bietti%2C%20assistant%20professor%20of%20law%20and%20computer%20science%20at%20Northeastern%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTransparency%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20could%20lead%20to%20better%20regulation%20of%20surveillance%20and%20behavioral%20advertising%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20a%20significant%20concern%20for%20privacy%20advocates%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2222fbad15-d850-486a-8c45-0310325ac6af%5C%22%3EA%20DOJ%20win%20isn't%20necessarily%20good%20news%20for%20all%20publishers%20and%20advertisers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20its%20lawyers%20are%20expected%20to%20argue%20in%20court%20that%20a%20breakup%20of%20its%20adtech%20stack%20would%20harm%20publishers%20and%20advertisers%20and%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20the%20company%20to%20invest%20in%20important%20research%20in%20areas%20like%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20barrier%20to%20entry%20to%20start%20advertising%20on%20Google%20Ads%20is%20incredibly%20low%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20why%20it%20has%20attracted%20so%20many%20small%20business%20advertisers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Jamison%2C%20director%20and%20professor%20of%20the%20Public%20Utility%20Research%20Center%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Digital%20Markets%20Initiative%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aei.org%2Ftechnology-and-innovation%2Fsmall-businesses-should-be-wary-of-a-breakup-of-google%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20breakup%20of%20Google%20and%20the%20resulting%20free-for-all%20from%20lower%20quality%20adtech%20players%20could%20result%20in%20higher%20ad%20prices%20and%20lower%20quality%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbsent%20evidence%20that%20Google%20is%20artificially%20restricting%20the%20quantity%20or%20quantity%20of%20ads%2C%20and%20that%20consumers%20would%20accept%20more%20ads%2C%20a%20breakup%20of%20Google's%20business%20will%20harm%20small%20businesses%20by%20removing%20their%20preferred%20advertising%20channel%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20publisher%20tech%20executive%2C%20who%20asked%20for%20anonymity%20to%20preserve%20business%20relationships%2C%20said%20while%20many%20in%20the%20publishing%20community%20are%20unhappy%20with%20some%20of%20Google's%20historical%20actions%2C%20a%20breakup%20might%20not%20be%20the%20best%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20executive%20said%20that%20if%20Google%20sold%20off%20its%20sell-side%20business%2C%20its%20DV360%20ad-buying%20platform%20might%20not%20have%20any%20incentive%20to%20continue%20spending%20on%20the%20open%20web%20and%20instead%20just%20direct%20even%20more%20ad%20dollars%20to%20Google's%20own%20platforms.%20Separately%2C%20they%20said%20that%20while%20a%20separation%20of%20Google's%20ad%20server%20and%20its%20ad%20exchange%20would%20be%20good%20for%20competition%20in%20the%20adtech%20market%2C%20it%20might%20drive%20ad%20server%20costs%20up%20for%20publishers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20ad%20server%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20loss%20leader%2C%20they%20make%20all%20their%20money%20in%20AdX%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20exec%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Google's%20ad%20exchange%20that%20connects%20buyers%20and%20sellers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22302448a4-afd4-4a39-b44d-78c9314e5f31%5C%22%3EGlobal%20regulators%20have%20Google%20in%20their%20sights%2C%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20unraveling%20of%20Google's%20ad%20empire%20would%20be%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20adtech%20company%20would%20still%20likely%20be%20worth%20billions%2C%20meaning%20any%20potential%20suitor%20with%20enough%20capital%20to%20acquire%20it%20would%20encounter%20its%20own%20competition%20issues.%20It's%20more%20likely%20that%20it%20would%20be%20spun%20off%20into%20a%20separate%20company.%20But%20then%20there's%20also%20the%20technical%20challenge%20of%20untangling%20assets%20that%2C%20by%20design%2C%20have%20become%20so%20intertwined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%2C%20experts%20generally%20think%20Google%20will%20probably%20come%20away%20from%20this%20trial%20with%20a%20bloody%20nose%20as%20regulators%20are%20increasingly%20taking%20a%20dim%20view%20of%20its%20advertising%20practices.%20The%20company%20recently%20lost%20a%20separate%20search%20ads%20antitrust%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20pond%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20said%20last%20year%20it%20might%20look%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Feu-says-it-may-seek-breakup-of-googles-ad-tech-business-b988fd78%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebreak%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20Google's%20adtech%20business.%20And%20just%20last%20Friday%2C%20the%20UK's%20competition%20watchdog%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.