but%20one%20election%20since%201984.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELichtman%20pays%20no%20attention%20to%20opinion%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20his%20predictions%20are%20based%20on%20a%20series%20of%20true-or-false%20propositions%20applied%20to%20the%20current%20presidential%20administration.%20If%20six%20or%20more%20of%20these%20%26quot%3Bkeys%26quot%3B%20are%20false%2C%20the%20election%20will%20go%20to%20the%20out-of-power%20challenger%20--%20in%20this%20case%2C%20Republican%20candidate%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESage%20of%20Bethesda%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20keys%2C%20for%20example%2C%20posits%20that%20the%20president's%20party%20won%20seats%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20midterm%20elections.%20The%20Democrats%20actually%20lost%20control%20of%20the%20House%20in%20the%202022%20midterms%2C%20meaning%20this%20particular%20key%20is%20termed%20%26quot%3Bfalse%2C%26quot%3B%20tipping%20the%20scales%20toward%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20more%20keys%20break%20Trump's%20way%3A%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20stepped%20down%2C%20meaning%20Democrats%20lost%20the%20key%20which%20determines%20the%20%26quot%3Bincumbency%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20vital%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden's%20vice%20president%20and%20replacement%20as%20nominee%2C%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20is%20surging%20on%20optimism%20among%20party%20faithful.%20But%20Lichtman%20rules%20that%20she%20does%20not%20qualify%20for%20another%20of%20the%20keys%2C%20which%20is%20being%20a%20charismatic%2C%20%26quot%3Bonce-in-a-generation%26quot%3B%20candidate%20in%20the%20style%20of%20Ronald%20Reagan%20or%20Franklin%20Roosevelt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20points%20to%20Trump%2C%20yes.%20But%20after%20that%20the%20keys%20start%20breaking%20in%20rapid%20succession%20for%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20massive%20environment%20and%20infrastructure%20legislation%20ticks%20the%20box%20for%20the%20key%20requiring%20a%20%26quot%3Bmajor%20policy%20change%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20current%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20for%20Harris%20is%20the%20exit%20of%20fringe%20independent%20candidate%20Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20satisfies%20the%20key%20demanding%20lack%20of%20major%20scandal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20the%20math%20and%20it%20turns%20out%20that%20only%20three%20keys%20are%20falling%20for%20Trump.%20But%20to%20be%20declared%20the%20presumptive%20winner%2C%20he%20would%20have%20needed%20six.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20another%20key%20which%20could%20go%20Harris's%20way%2C%20if%20the%20administration%20reaches%20a%20ceasefire%20and%20hostage%20release%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20move%20that%20would%20likely%20require%20Democrats%20to%20push%20harder%20against%20the%20Israeli%20government%20--%20sure%20to%20cause%20strain%20among%20poll-obsessed%20advisors%20in%20a%20party%20trying%20to%20straddle%20a%20base%20that%20is%20heavily%20divided%20over%20the%20issue.%20Yet%2C%20a%20ceasefire%20would%20mean%20the%20Democrats%20actually%20delivered%20a%20policy%20achievement%2C%20Lichtman%20argues%2C%20and%20deliver%20one%20of%20the%20keys%20on%20foreign%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20like%20to%20speculate%2C%20because%20the%20devil%20is%20in%20the%20details%2C%20but%20that%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20big%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EForget%20the%20'noise'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B13%20keys%26quot%3B%20home%20in%20on%20the%20speculative%20nature%20of%20some%20of%20the%20true-false%20propositions.%20What%20is%20a%20charismatic%20leader%2C%20for%20example%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20sage%20of%20Bethesda%2C%20as%20some%20have%20dubbed%20him%2C%20is%20well-versed%20in%20arguing%20his%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20doing%20this%20for%2040%20years.%20I%20think%20I've%20heard%20every%20conceivable%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3B'Aren't%20your%20keys%20subjective%3F'%20I%20obviously%20have%20an%20answer%20to%20that%20--%20they're%20not%20subjective%2C%20they're%20judgmental.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20dealing%20with%20human%20beings.%20Historians%20make%20judgments%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20the%20judgments%20are%20very%20tightly%20constrained.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20%26quot%3Bnoise%26quot%3B%20of%20national%20political%20punditry%2C%20Lichtman%20argues%2C%20presidential%20elections%20are%20a%20simple%20%26quot%3Bvote%20up%20or%20down%20on%20the%20strength%20and%20performance%20of%20the%20White%20House%20party.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20way%2C%20his%20method%20is%20anti-horse%20race%20--%20focused%20on%20good%20governance%20rather%20than%20campaigns%2C%20since%20in%20reality%20%26quot%3Bwe%20forget%20virtually%20anything%20a%20candidate%20has%20to%20say.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20election%20where%20Lichtman's%20calculations%20did%20not%20predict%20the%20president%20was%20the%202000%20victory%20of%20George%20W.%20Bush.%20Lichtman%20can%20defend%20his%20record%20by%20pointing%20out%20that%20this%20was%20a%20legally%20complicated%20nail-biter%20in%20which%20Democrat%20Al%20Gore%20won%20the%20popular%20vote%20but%20Bush%20took%20victory%20courtesy%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725865260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fugf3uu1g_trump-harris-_625x300_22_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fkamala-harris-vs-donald-trump-historians-13-key-method-predicts-a-kamala-harris-win-in-us-election-6523545%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Forget%20the%20polls%2C%20ditch%20the%20data%20and%20stop%20sending