%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDUSU%20elections%20are%20conducted%20through%20direct%20voting%20by%20students%20from%20the%20university%20and%20its%20affiliated%20colleges%2C%20typically%20held%20between%20August%20and%20September%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Will%20Elections%20Be%20Held%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20polls%20will%20be%20conducted%20on%20September%2027.%20The%20votes%20will%20be%20counted%20on%20September%2028.%20Voting%20will%20take%20place%20for%20day-time%20classes%20between%208.30am%20and%201pm%2C%20and%20for%20evening%20classes%20from%203pm%20to%207.30pm%2C%20as%20per%20the%20official%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%20University%20Students%20Union%202023%3A%20Winners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20RSS-affiliated%20ABVP%20won%20three%20central%20panel%20positions%2C%20including%20the%20presidency%2C%20while%20the%20Congress'%20student%20wing%2C%20NSUI%2C%20secured%20the%20vice-presidency.%20The%20elections%20were%20held%20after%20a%20gap%20of%20three%20years%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ABVP%20won%20three%20seats%20(president%2C%20secretary%2C%20joint%20secretary).%20The%20National%20Students'%20Union%20of%20India%20(NSUI)%20won%20the%20vice-president%20post%20in%20the%202023%20DUSU%20elections.%20Tushar%20Dedha%20from%20ABVP%20won%20the%20president's%20post%2C%20Abhi%20Dahiya%20from%20NSUI%20won%20the%20vice-president%20post%2C%20Aprajita%20from%20ABVP%20won%20the%20secretary%20post%2C%20and%20Sachin%20Basla%20won%20the%20joint%20secretary%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20DUSU%20elections%20before%202023%20were%20held%20in%202019.%20Polls%20were%20not%20held%20in%202020%20and%202021%20due%20to%20COVID-19%2C%20while%20possible%20disruptions%20to%20the%20academic%20calendar%20prevented%20the%202022%20elections.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725857940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F201